        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FATHOM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FAMOUS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FABRIC</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">�� Key Takeaway</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">FA provides <span class="text-white font-medium">800+ words with the highest average score among F-pairs</span>. FACTORY (15 pts) and FATHOM (14 pts) are premium plays. Short words like FAD (7 pts) and FACT (9 pts) efficiently deploy the F tile while keeping your rack flexible.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-qu" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Containing QU — Essential Scrabble Q Words</span></a>
